Name:
System internal name of the parameter.  

Parameter are allowed to have the same name, as long as the attributes are different.  The HID and ID columns determine uniqueness.
ID:
Parameter Definition Identifier

This is the "global" identifier for the parameter.  It should be UNIQUE and STATIC among all parameters as it will be used to identify this parameter within other spreadsheets / contexts.  There is outstanding debate as to if this ID should be a simple incrementing ID (as below) or a computable SHA style identifier.
HID:
Human-Readable Identifier

CALCULATED from the following attributes of a parameter:  Name, Parameter Type, Value Encoding, and Unit of Measure

Intended for rapid comparison of parameters by a human.  NOT utilized programmatically for comparison.  May be used to calculate the ID.

MUST be unique - if not, will be indicated in the Conflict column
HID Conflict: Formula to detect duplication of a parameter (HID) within this spreadsheet.  If the row is unique, the cell will contain a 0.  If a row is a duplicate, the cell will turn green and contain a positive # indicating the # of conflicting parameters.
Parameter Type: Member of the code set ParameterType
Value Encoding:
The encoding of the value.  Typically an intrinsic type.  'opaque' indicates an undefined value encoding and is stored as raw bits (blob)

If the Parameter Type is 'category', the value encoding should match the encoding of the KEY
Code Set:
If the Parameter Type is "category", this column holds the definition of the key:value map of meanings

"Code Set" is the general term for an Enumeration

Remember to have the fill value as a category
Fill Value: A value used to represent missing or undefined data. Please ensure that the fill_value is NOT a valid value for the parameter. For example, 0 is typically a very poor fill_value since it is usually valid (i.e. for temp, lat, lon, pressure, salinity, etc).
Display Name: The expected display name for R2.1 and beyond. Will be a required field in R2.1 and beyond. May not be used in 2.0
Precision:
This column should contain the decimal precision that the UI Charts/Tables will utilize to display the appropriate values.

If a precision is not known, leave it blank (it will still use the default).  If the default is to be used (currently precision of 5 decimal digits), and its approved to use whatever the default value is, set the value to "default".  If the value is not a float, the value should be set to 0.
Standard Name: The CF Standard Name for this parameter: http://cf-pcmdi.llnl.gov/documents/cf-standard-names/standard-name-table/20/cf-standard-name-table.html
Data Product Identifier: OOI Data Product Identifier as defined in SAF
Reference URLS: List of URLS to parameter documentation
Description: A human-readable description of the parameter.
Review Status: Parameters must be reviewed for accuracy and completeness by an individual other than the parameter author. Please indicate when a parameter, or group of parameters are "ready for review" in this column. After review is complete, the reviewer should mark the column as "Review Complete", or "Review Issue" .
Long Name: CF Long Name. A long descriptive name, which may be used, for example, for labeling plots.

Name: salinity

Name: salinity
Description: Measure of absolute salinity adopted and defined jointly by the Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission (IOC), International Association for the Physical Sciences of the Oceans (IAPSO) and the Scientific Committee on Oceanic Research (SCOR) in 2010.  Absolute Salinity represents, to the best available accuracy, the mass fraction of dissolved solute in a sample of Standard Seawater of the same density as the observed sample. Description: Reveals if the temperature compensation is calculated using the Stern-Volmer-Uchida formula.  The OOI DOCONCS DPS requires the use of the the SVU equation.

Name: sampling_interval
Description: The interval in seconds at which samples are taken.

Name: location_description
Description: User entered text about the instrument location (non geographic, see geographic position).

Name: geographic_position_description
Description: User entered text about the geographic position of the instrument.

Name: vertical_position_description
Description: User entered vertical position of the instrument.

Name: reference_description
Description: User entered text for references.

Name: eastward_wind_velocity
Display Name: Eastward Wind Velocity relative to Magnetic North

Name: northward_wind_velocity
Display Name: Northward Wind Velocity relative to Magnetic North

Name: sampling_state
Description: A sampling status message of 'GO' if sampling or 'STOPPED' if not sampling.

Name: eastward_wind_velocity_l1
Display Name: Eastward Wind Velocity relative to True North

Name: northward_wind_velocity_l1
Display Name: Northward Wind Velocity relative to True North

Name: elapsed_time
Display Name: Elapsed Time since start of sample, s

Name: sampling_status_code
Code Set: {0:'Pumping in progress', 1:'Volume reached', 2:'Time limit reached', 3:'Min flow reached', 4:'Low battery', 5:'Stopped by user', 6:'Pump would not start', 7:'Sudden flow obstruction', 8:'Sudden obstruction with slip', 9:'Sudden pressure release', -99:'empty'}

Name: instrument_id
Description: SAT + instrument type

Name: serial_number
Description: SPKIR serial number

Name: timer
Description: number of seconds that have passed since the end of the initialization sequence.

Name: sample_delay
Description: representing the number of milliseconds to offset the Timer value to give an accurate indication of when the frameâs sensors were sampled

Name: channel_1
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the first optical channel

Name: channel_2
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the second optical channel

Name: channel_3
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the third optical channel

Name: channel_4
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the forth optical channel

Name: channel_5
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the fifth optical channel

Name: channel_6
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the sixth optical channel

Name: channel_7
Description: value representing the sampled A/D counts from the seventh optical channel

Name: vin_sense
Description: regulated input voltage

Name: va_sense
Description: analog rail voltage for the operational components of the instrument

Name: internal_temperature
Description: internal temperature of the instrument

Name: frame_counter
Description: count of each frame transmitted

Name: checksum
Description: check sum on the telemetry frame

Name: telemetry_baud_rate
Description: data transfer rate on telemetry interface in bits per second (bps)

Name: max_frame_rate
Description: Defines the maximum frame rate that the instrument will use during normal operations (in other words, the sample rate).

Name: initialize_silent_mode
Description: Enables/disables display of start-up banner during initialization sequence when instrument is powered up. Default is "on".

Name: initialize_power_down
Description: Enables/disables application of operational power at end of initialization sequence. Default is "off".

Name: initialize_auto_telemetry
Description: Enables/Disables auto, or free-running, sampling once normal operations begin. Default is "on". With this mode off, polled sampling is available.

Name: network_mode
Description: Enables/disables network operation (Satlantic Network, not Ethernet!) for the instrument. Default is "off".

Name: network_address
Description: Satlantic Network address. Valid range is 1 - 255.

Name: network_baud_rate
Description: Network baud rate.

Name: external_device2_fault
Description: External Fault, Device 2 boolean.

Name: external_device3_fault
Description: External Fault, Device 3 boolean.
